          "body": "Three times Jesus warns that the unbelieving will *die in their sin* (8:21, 24 twice). The phrase is precise: not 'die *because of* sin' (true but distinct) but 'die *in* sin' — unforgiven, unsaved, with the sin still on them at the moment of death. The condition for escaping this end is exactly stated: *unless you believe that I am He* (8:24). The pastoral force is severe. The chapter forecloses the possibility of dying in peace while rejecting Christ; there is no neutral middle. This warning to the religious establishment in the temple is one of the New Testament's clearest articulations that religious lineage, ceremonial observance, and even initial belief (8:31) do not save apart from abiding faith in the *I AM*."
